<item>
            <title>[LU-10448] policy to pick a primary for mirrored write</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10448</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;For a mirrored file, when it is written at the first time, the policy to pick a replica as primary is primitive, either it just chooses the first replica or a random one. A policy function should be defined for replica choosing. At least it should avoid the replicas with unavailable OSTs.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
